fields.name: Cereals
fields.description: Grains cultivated for their edible starchy seeds, forming a staple food source worldwide.

fields.name: Legumes
fields.description: Plants in the family Fabaceae known for nitrogen-fixing root nodules and protein-rich seeds.

fields.name: Vegetables
fields.description: Herbaceous plants cultivated for their edible leaves, roots, stems, or fruits.

fields.name: Fruits
fields.description: Plants cultivated for their sweet or savory edible fruits.

fields.name: Oilseeds
fields.description: Crops grown primarily for oil extraction from their seeds.

fields.name: Wheat
fields.description: One of the most widely cultivated cereal grains, used for bread, pasta, and pastry production.

fields.name: Rice
fields.description: A staple cereal grain for more than half of the world's population, grown in flooded paddies.

fields.name: Corn
fields.description: A versatile cereal crop used for food, animal feed, and ethanol production.

fields.name: Soybean
fields.description: A high-protein legume widely used in food products and as animal feed.

fields.name: Lentil
fields.description: A lens-shaped pulse rich in protein and iron, commonly used in soups and stews.

fields.name: Chickpea
fields.description: A protein-rich legume used in hummus, falafel, and many traditional dishes worldwide.

fields.name: Tomato
fields.description: A widely cultivated fruit used as a vegetable, rich in lycopene and vitamins.

fields.name: Carrot
fields.description: A root vegetable rich in beta-carotene, typically orange in color.

fields.name: Strawberry
fields.description: A sweet, red fruit prized for its flavor and nutritional value.

fields.name: Sunflower
fields.description: A tall flowering plant grown for its oil-rich seeds and ornamental value.
